<p>The estate is situated off the Edgware road near the Regentâ€™s Canal. It sits <a href="https://lbhf.maps.arcgis.com/apps/webappviewer/index.html?id=7cab3cdf6e344a0fb24df59ed6b9bdc5">within</a> an area that has been designated a <strong>Housing Renewal</strong> zone in Westminsterâ€™s <a href="https://www.westminster.gov.uk/cityplan2040">draft 2019-2040 Local Plan</a>.</p>

<p><img src="/images/renewalarea.png" class="img-fluid rounded img-thumbnail" /></p>

<p>It is also within the boundary of the <strong>Edgeware Road Housing Zone</strong>, one of <a href="https://www.london.gov.uk/what-we-do/housing-and-land/increasing-housing-supply/housing-zones#acc-i-42741">30 special housing zones</a> designated by the Mayor to deliver accelerated housing development. The Edgeware Road zone is expected to deliver 1700 new homes.</p>

<p>The estate has already been subject to a small amount of in-fill development, with <a href="https://www.westminster.gov.uk/parsons-north-development">60 homes delivered</a> on open space at the foot of Parsons House.</p>
